</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biyomedikal Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6247</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 324</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Medical Imaging</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The course covers the most important imaging modalities in radiology: projection radiography, x-ray computed tomography, nuclear medicine, ultrasound imaging, and magnetic resonance imaging</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412515&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biyomedikal Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6247</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 328</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Characterizaion Methods for Biomaterials</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Within the scope of the course, information is given about the physical, chemical, mechanical, morphological properties of biomaterials and the characterization methods for measuring and monitoring their biological activities. Each week, homework or quizzes are made to follow the course topics. In the laboratory studies, the characteristic properties of polymeric and metallic biomaterials, and the analysis of scaffolds such as hydrogels are made. In these experiments carried out as a team, a team member each week controls the experiment as the team leader. Interpretation of measurement results obtained in reports or data such as spectrum is provided. At the end of the semester, each student makes a brief presentation on a characterization/measurement method that was not covered in the course.
Also, at the last week of the semester, a visit to a laboratory will be planned. This would be either a hospital or a company related to the instruments/methods covered in this course.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412542&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
